benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles - Retrieve a bundle by external key

covered: Valid Request: Happy path (TC01) exercises successful retrieval for a valid externalKey.
Empty Response: Scenarios for missing data and non-existent keys (TC08, TC16) are covered.
Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of valid/invalid combinations (externalKey, includedDeleted, audit).
Authorization: Tests for unauthorized (TC11) and forbidden (TC12) access are included.
Server Errors/Resilience: Scenarios for database unavailability (TC13), service downtime (TC28), and transient issues (TC21) are present.

Data Integrity and Edge Cases: Covers deleted items (TC02, TC06), audit field variations (TC03, TC04, TC05), duplicates and data anomalies (TC14, TC27), security edge cases (TC19, TC20), encoding/unicode (TC23), max/min length (TC24, TC25), empty parameter handling (TC29), and response structure/content checks (TC30).
Concurrency/Scale: Concurrent requests (TC18) and large datasets (TC27) are addressed.
gaps: Pagination: No tests explicitly verify pagination behavior when multiple bundles exist or when paginating results.
Caching/ETag: No scenarios validating caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No tests assessing throttling or rate-limiting behavior under bursty requests.
Detailed error messaging: Some 400/404 bodies are described at a high level but no explicit verification of exact error payload structures across all error cases.
Very large-scale performance: While TC27 covers 10,000 bundles, there is no explicit load/stress testing scenario beyond a single large-case retrieval.
recommendations: Add a dedicated pagination scenario to validate proper paging, page size, and total counts when many bundles match.
Add tests to assert caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) and verify client-side caching behavior.
Introduce rate-limiting/throttle tests to ensure proper handling under high request rates.
Enhance error payload validation across all error scenarios to assert exact fields and messages.
Include an explicit load/stress test under realistic concurrency to observe latency under sustained load.
